cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on the use of facial expressions as evaluative feedback in interactive reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The implementation of the TAMER framework in a reinforcement learning benchmark problem and the use of a CNN-RNN model for analysis suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of facial expressions also involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Finally, the study involves the training of agents, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
